1
00:00:00,222 --> 00:00:01,628
Previously on Jericho.

2
00:00:01,765 --> 00:00:03,775
<i>So I hear you and I
are going to be partners now.</i>

3
00:00:03,776 --> 00:00:04,818
<i>Where'd you get that?</i>

4
00:00:04,819 --> 00:00:07,190
<i>You're running the store,
you're going to need protection.</i>

5
00:00:08,709 --> 00:00:10,560
<i>Don't make the same mistake
that Gracie made.</i>

6
00:00:10,561 --> 00:00:12,561
<i>Or those people out there
are going to be putting</i>

7
00:00:12,562 --> 00:00:14,364
<i>flowers and candles
on the sidewalk for you.</i>

8
00:00:16,144 --> 00:00:17,166
<i>Who the hell is that?</i>

9
00:00:24,354 --> 00:00:25,834
<i>Remember,
the gas tank on this thing</i>

10
00:00:25,835 --> 00:00:27,075
<i>is on the left-hand side,</i>

11
00:00:27,076 --> 00:00:29,047
<i>so if somebody decides
to start shooting at you,</i>

12
00:00:29,048 --> 00:00:30,405
<i>make sure it's not on that side.</i>

13
00:00:30,406 --> 00:00:31,590
<i>Okay. Anything else?</i>

14
00:00:37,283 --> 00:00:39,853
<i>So, are we going to see you
for Thanksgiving?</i>

15
00:00:40,109 --> 00:00:42,657
<i>Well, I think Mary and I
are going to spend it together.</i>

16
00:00:42,658 --> 00:00:43,885
<i>Well, you're always welcome.</i>

17
00:00:43,886 --> 00:00:46,501
<i>Thanks, but I don't want to put
you guys in an awkward position.</i>

18
00:00:46,502 --> 00:00:49,311
<i>You could have thought of that before
you moved in with your mistress</i>

19
00:00:49,312 --> 00:00:50,642
<i>and left your wife with us.</i>

20
00:00:52,019 --> 00:00:53,339
<i>Some of them were on planes</i>

21
00:00:53,340 --> 00:00:54,842
<i>that landed in the middle of nowhere.</i>

22
00:00:55,459 --> 00:00:56,796
<i>They've been walking for weeks.</i>

23
00:00:57,326 --> 00:00:58,868
<i>They must have gone through hell.</i>

24
00:00:59,113 --> 00:01:00,149
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

25
00:01:05,242 --> 00:01:06,243
<i>Is it really you?</i>

26
00:01:06,980 --> 00:01:09,105
<i>I need you to keep the kids
in the house for a while</i>

27
00:01:09,106 --> 00:01:10,399
<i>until I can sort something out.</i>

28
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,697
<i>Are we in danger, Robert?</i>

29
00:01:13,350 --> 00:01:15,534
<i>You have moderate frostbite
on your toes and fingers.</i>

30
00:01:15,535 --> 00:01:17,284
<i>You need to keep them
clean and warm.</i>

31
00:01:18,213 --> 00:01:19,459
<i>Do you have a place to stay?</i>

32
00:01:20,774 --> 00:01:22,306
<i>Do you know anyone in Jericho?</i>

33
00:01:25,153 --> 00:01:26,161
<i>Actually,</i>

34
00:01:26,893 --> 00:01:27,897
<i>I do.</i>

35
00:01:38,103 --> 00:01:39,531
It's freezing in here, too.

36
00:01:40,187 --> 00:01:41,190
Mr. Bintner?

37
00:01:45,724 --> 00:01:46,804
Mr. Bintner?

38
00:01:52,089 --> 00:01:53,189
Joe?

39
00:02:18,288 --> 00:02:20,391
The temperature dropped so fast.

40
00:02:24,326 --> 00:02:26,274
It's going to be a long winter.

41
00:02:26,303 --> 00:02:28,329
All right, everyone!
Everyone, please!

42
00:02:28,715 --> 00:02:29,718
Please!

43
00:02:29,719 --> 00:02:30,933
Right now,

44
00:02:30,934 --> 00:02:33,267
we're using the generator
to power the town hall

45
00:02:33,268 --> 00:02:35,544
for three hours a day,
and the Med Center for six.

46
00:02:36,084 --> 00:02:38,727
And this is how much fuel we have,

47
00:02:39,286 --> 00:02:41,081
and this is how much we need

48
00:02:41,082 --> 00:02:42,470
to get us through the winter.

49
00:02:42,759 --> 00:02:44,978
At current levels of consumption,

50
00:02:45,441 --> 00:02:47,833
we will be completely
out of gas and diesel

51
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:48,933
in two weeks.

52
00:02:49,483 --> 00:02:51,354
I wonder when the dancing girls show up.

53
00:02:51,355 --> 00:02:52,357
Stop.

54
00:02:52,358 --> 00:02:55,782
There's a way of doing this without
scaring the crap out of everybody.

55
00:02:55,859 --> 00:02:57,016
He was elected.

56
00:02:57,486 --> 00:02:58,895
Guess he's going to do it his way.

57
00:02:59,821 --> 00:03:01,075
I'm going to need a hobby.

58
00:03:01,076 --> 00:03:02,416
So here's what we're working on.

59
00:03:02,734 --> 00:03:04,721
All right, we got
organized firewood crews...

60
00:03:04,846 --> 00:03:06,428
- Mr. Hawkins?
- Yeah.

61
00:03:06,486 --> 00:03:08,454
There's a woman
in that group of refugees

62
00:03:08,455 --> 00:03:10,750
that Bill is processing,
I think you should talk to her.

63
00:03:10,751 --> 00:03:11,966
Why?

64
00:03:11,967 --> 00:03:14,146
She said she used to be
a cop in Saint Louis.

65
00:03:15,014 --> 00:03:18,371
Especially with 53
new people among us,

66
00:03:18,410 --> 00:03:20,763
we have got to start rethinking things,

67
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:22,442
fast,

68
00:03:22,616 --> 00:03:24,198
or the people we lost last night

69
00:03:24,199 --> 00:03:26,455
won't be the only casualties
of this coming winter.

70
00:03:26,456 --> 00:03:27,970
What about the windmills?

71
00:03:28,086 --> 00:03:29,089
She's right.

72
00:03:29,841 --> 00:03:31,095
Wind power.

73
00:03:31,694 --> 00:03:33,372
We should be building windmills.

74
00:03:33,373 --> 00:03:34,385
Harry?

75
00:03:34,386 --> 00:03:36,581
I think you all know Harry Carmichael,

76
00:03:36,582 --> 00:03:38,317
our chief engineer
down at the mine.

77
00:03:38,318 --> 00:03:41,175
We've been looking into wind turbines
for weeks now with Mayor Green.

78
00:03:41,176 --> 00:03:43,818
But in order to build anything
that can be connected to the grid,

79
00:03:43,819 --> 00:03:45,284
it's going to take time.

80
00:03:45,448 --> 00:03:47,590
Time I'm not sure we can afford.

81
00:03:53,290 --> 00:03:55,895
- She's in here.
- Thanks, Jimmy.

82
00:04:01,692 --> 00:04:03,351
Hello, Rob.

83
00:04:06,091 --> 00:04:07,461
Any parts we don't have...

84
00:04:07,462 --> 00:04:09,815
we simply don't have
the maching capabilities.

85
00:04:09,816 --> 00:04:11,397
What kind of parts?

86
00:04:11,764 --> 00:04:14,041
Mechanical governors to regulate output.

87
00:04:14,427 --> 00:04:17,166
With the EMP damage, we're figuring
out a lot of this from scratch.

88
00:04:17,167 --> 00:04:20,041
- It's still a long way off.
- Black Jack Fairgrounds.

89
00:04:21,171 --> 00:04:23,296
We walked through it
on our way back here.

90
00:04:23,525 --> 00:04:24,865
It's become a trading post.

91
00:04:24,866 --> 00:04:27,383
People from all over
the region are trading...

92
00:04:27,776 --> 00:04:29,443
food, information,

93
00:04:29,704 --> 00:04:31,012
machine parts.

94
00:04:31,623 --> 00:04:32,800
They may have what we need.

95
00:04:32,803 --> 00:04:34,519
That's got to be a 200-mile drive.

96
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:36,246
That's a lot of gas for a "maybe."

97
00:04:36,343 --> 00:04:38,234
If we can get one windmill working,

98
00:04:38,235 --> 00:04:39,989
we'd save that much gas in a month.

99
00:04:40,490 --> 00:04:43,346
If we get enough of them,
we could be off gas for good.

100
00:04:44,021 --> 00:04:45,622
It might not be a bad idea

101
00:04:45,623 --> 00:04:47,677
to put a small party together
and go check it out.

102
00:04:48,439 --> 00:04:50,407
Is anyone interested
in volunteering?

103
